name: Big Wall Greg's Chicken Shack
description: Relatively low angle route with good hands and feet.

name: Don't Mess with the Bull
description: On the outside of the tower, 18' left of the hallway entrance

name: Echolocation
description: Pull on slopey holds and work your way up a large flake feature. Traverse left and up though large holds to the anchor.Â

name: Piss Ant
description: This route starts on Which Side Are You On? but after the third bolt use the left line to stay off of Big Wall Greg's Chicken Shack.

name: Point Blank
description: A classic as far as I know.  Solid Rock!!!

name: Spiders From Mars
description: This route is located between Big Wall Greg's Chicken Shack and Venom.  Go straight up through the slab.

name: Spirit
description: This route is located on the backside of the Jimmy boulder. Scramble up the large boulder by Chimichonga to reach the start of the route.

name: Stinger Direct
description: Right of Venom.  Start on rock and climb straight up.

name: Venom
description: The physical crux is down low, but the mental crux is the upper slab.  Pull a couple easy moves to the crux.  Pull over the lip to super thin and technical slab climbing at it's finest.

name: The Voice
description: Climbs the far Right arete of the Jimmy block. Awesome pocket climbing on an exposed arete. Super technical climbing.

name: Which Side Are You On?
description: This route works up the Arete to the left of Big Wall Greg's Chicken Shack.  Cut right back onto Greg's after the fourth bolt to keep it at .10c.

name: Chimichonga
description: About 12' left of Lucky, stem the hallway, commit to the main wall and follow the sport line.

name: Lucky Bastard
description: Good jam crack that climbs a corner through a short wider section and then traverses out underneath a roof. A bit burly for the grade but a fun trad route.

name: Luscious Babes
description: Still in the main hallway, it's the long clean slab down the slope and left of Screamery.  Fun route.

name: Off Web
description: Easy start lay backing to an off width crux about 2/3s of the way up. Probably doesn't see a lot of traffic.

name: Screamery
description: Scramble up the lower angle corner slab.    An ok diversion and a reasonable way to set a TR on an adjacent route, providing one is solid at the grade.    Nice rock.

name: Cats in the Cradle
description: Pull down on the holds, and go up. Another classic pocket-pulling adventure.

name: Cougar Love
description: Start with some fun pocket pulling, reach a burly, reachy stand-up single move crux, that seemed to me to be somewhat improbable for 5.11, and continue romping up to the anchors.

name: Dance with Destiny
description: Climb bulge and pockets to a bulge with great pocket with a shallow crack above,(crux) a very trickyÂ  crux,

name: Left of the Arete
description: A good introductory 5.10, with a single move that might be 10a mixed in with a lot of fun, juggy 5.8/5.9 climbing.

name: Unknown
description: Fun and steep 5.9 climbing pulling over multiple bulges. Very similar in character to the next 5.9 to the right, and that route could easily be toproped from the same anchor as this one.

name: Unknown (Bolted Chimney)
description: Time to drop that brush and those Solutions and lace up your TC pros because what your lucky gym rat ass has just stumbled upon is a sport bolted chimney. Very forgiving for chimney climbing, and surprisingly quite enjoyable.  Crux is likely getting off the ground, otherwise things seem to get progressively easier the higher you get...depending on your body size of course.  --  Can also be led on gear by squeezing farther in, which would make it almost an entirely separate route...

name: Unknown 2
description: More fun, steep 5.9 climbing, starts of with some steep jug hauling then pull over some more bulges.

name: Everybody Needs Friends
description: Same start as Tasmania Devil, but climb left at 3rd bolt.  Great route, with fun pumpy moves.

name: The Fall of Legends
description: Fun climbing until the last bolt, then things go south. No idea what you're supposed to do here, but whatever you do you're gonna need a wire brush because everything up above the last bolt is filthy and covered in moss and dirt (as of 10/12/15). But its only for about two moves. Have fun.

name: Flingin Hog
description: Climb is in the corner left of the Beaver Wall.  Fun moves to the top!  A good route to warm up on for the rest of the hard routes.

name: Frizzle Fry
description: Start halfway between the crack and the corner.  Good climb.

name: Legend of the Falls
description: Another hard route to finish of this pumpy wall.  Left most climb on wall.  Climb left of the big tree.

name: Mod Squad
description: Easy route left of "Flingin' the Hog", warm up for the area. Fun moves, I did alot of palming.

name: Red Corvette
description: A great hard route for someone who wants to sample the goods.  Climb starts in grey streak 20ft left of crack, and climbs right of the big tree.

name: Shorty the Pimp
description: Climb is just right of the crack.  Move right on to the face.  Hard would be a good way to explain it.

name: Spits or Swallows
description: Easy 5.11 climbing to mantle...should have ended at the lip for a better route.

name: Tasmania Devil
description: Start 6 ft. right of corner and go right at the 3rd bolt.  Fun!

name: Unknown warmup
description: New route between Mod Squad and Flinging the Hog. Â The start is pretty easy, so itâs easy to mistake for Mod if you donât know the area/have a guidebook. Â Felt a bit harder than Mod, maybe 9+/10-. Â Tricky crux pulling the bulge.

name: Who Needs Friends
description: Overhung the whole way.  Make awkward hard moves to full body rest 20' feet up.  Take a deep breath and climb the steep crack using jams and face holds to a pumpy and slightly run-out finish above bomber gear.   The route is called "Who Needs Friends" because it was bolted.  IMHO I think it climbs nicely as a trad route.

name: Alaska
description: This route is located just to the left of Express Checkout Line and use the same entrance.  Has a low and balancy crux.

name: Big Star
description: A little more continous than Glaxay 500 and Sun Ra. We travel the spaceways bad and beautiful

name: Birthday Route
description: This is a tricky little climb that is located on the semi-pillar towards the end of Big Star.

name: Chit Chat
description: Past Beaver wall, a sweet dihedral crack in the corner.

name: Cocoa Rae
description: This route is the first bolted line to the left of Birthday Route.

name: Conspiracy Theorists
description: Climb this mixed route and clip bolts when you can. Keep looking for good gear placements as you go up.Â

name: Da Bro
description: This route is located just to the right of Birthday Route and features a low crux.

name: Express Checkout Line
description: A very reach dependent low crux.  This route is just to the left of Cocoa Rae.  Traverse in on the ledge or climb up through the slab to access the first bolt on the bulge.

name: Free day
description: Obvious vertical crack in the center of Big Star Wall.

name: Galaxy 500
description: 20ft left of Mary's Cookies.  Technical pocket start to the right-leaning crack 15ft up.  Pockets to horizontals to a halfway jug that starts the techy slab to the anchors.

name: Get Out of My Kitchen
description: Left ward arching crack that leads into Chit Chat.

name: Ladybug Lynn
description: This is the line bolted to the left of Alaska.  Use the same entrance.

name: Mary's Cookies
description: Amazing slab/face on the right side of the big star wall.  The one with the spacy bolts.  The cruxes are well protected.  Movement is technical folowing the diagonal seam.

name: Mr. Allison's Cookies
description: High quality with interesting movement

name: Stingray
description: Start at the right end of an obvious rounded ledge.  Route angles slightly left at start.

name: Sun Ra
description: Battle through the first 20 feet to an easier section. Balance and finesse right then up through a shollow corner, (sexy/cruxy), to easier ground.    Four stars compared to most of the Falls but not quiet as good as Wishbone and Big Star

name: Unknown Chimney (L of Birthday Route)
description: Somewhat featured and remarkably straightforward chimney climbing, I thought this was really pretty fun. Would be a great route to put beginner rock climbers on.

name: Wishbone
description: Fairly sustained route with a distinct crux about half way up

name: After-Hours
description: Begin in a broken, right-facing dihedral system. Climb 20 feet up, 20 feet to the left, and 20 more feet up. Mantle on to the upper ramp and belay on small gear. The second pitch consists of a scramble up the ramp, past a bolt to the anchors.

name: Blazed Of Glory Project
description: There is no anchor equipped on this project. Climb the red face through blank sections.Â

name: Gobble Juice
description: Climb up the overhanging flake and finish on the headway all. Watch out for the pump!

name: Jones'n In Jacksonville
description: Hard crimpy holds and a few pockets. Stay strong on this one.Â

name: Manufacturing Consent
description: It's the next route on the rounded corner, 30' left of Ladybug Lynn.  Veer right at the 2nd clip.

name: Mason Dixon Line
description: Climb up and through the weirdly shaped hueco in the center of the face. A few cruxes on this one, its not over till its over.Â

name: No Paynes In Heaven
description: Climb the dihedral crack until it ends. Stem your way to the anchor after that.Â

name: PITA
description: Meander up the beautiful face left of No Paynes in Heaven.

name: Project
description: Currently there are no anchors equipped on this project. Have fun figuring out the sequence.Â

name: Raging Intensity
description: GREAT arete route, very technical.

name: Reduction
description: It is noted that the first bolt should be stick clipped.   Beginning off a small boulder, reach over left and grab the starting hold and follow bolts to the top.Â

name: Tear Stained Eye
description: Tricky Techy at the bottom

name: Train in Vain
description: Dirty bottom, fun top.

name: Underoos for Kangaroos
description: Roughly 60' left of Tear Stained Eye.  Bulgy route.

name: Working Class
description: This route begins climbing up a right angling seam. Before getting into the overhang, you encounter a low crux on thin holds. After battling the overhang, you gain the face to encounter an even more challenging finish on more thin holds till the top. It's not over till it's over!

name: Zen Arcade
description: Shares the first few bolts with Manufacturing consent and moves up through the overhang with a difficult sequence at the lip. Mantel after the roof to bigger holds. Several difficults sections.

name: Both Sides of the Story
description: Start matched on horn and go straight up through face.

name: Duckpin Crack
description: Short and fat and fun. Use just the offwidth crack to get up to the lip of the boulder and top out.

name: Exponentials
description: Start by walking your feet up the obvious ramp feature. At 10' there is a large ledge. Choose a final move to get over the lip. Fun and varied.

name: The Huck
description: Start matched on ledge at edge of roof. Campus, dyno, or foot jump your way to the lip.    Potential low start looks quite hard and holds look friable.

name: The Hug
description: Sit start in the pit and squeeze and shift your way up the prow. Cool and challenging.

name: The Impossible Kid
description: Start matched on flake at chest height, head straight up to topout.

name: Knock First
description: Sit start on flake low and right, follow juggy flake holds slightly left then straight up. Choose holds carefully, holds on the left side of feature are delicate.

name: Low Earth Orbit
description: Use your head, shoulders, knees, and toes to overcome gravity on this one. Maybe pack a booster rocket or two!    Start matched on the right side of the big ledge under the boulder and work straight up the sloping pockets until you're standing on the small ledge at head height.

name: Mickey
description: Sit start at left end of ledge, work straight up nice pockets to crux at top out

name: Problem 1
description: Start matched in hole to the right.

name: Problem 2
description: Sit start in hole on left side of face. Work up to horizontal and finish same as problem 1. Don't fall in the water.

name: Tapeworms
description: Work straight up the slabby face on nice holds.

name: Whisker britches
description: Start at the bottom left side of the boulder on right hand iron flake crimp gaston and left hand edge. Follow the lip up and right using a combination of slopers pockets and edges eventually topping out on the tallest point of the boulder.

name: Animal Husbandry
description: Take the right top-out.

name: Belching Fiance
description: Left top-out of Animal Husbandry.

name: The Big Easy
description: Climb up this steep face using hold that get smaller as you climb higher. Move up and left near the 5th bolt.Â

name: The Easier Variation
description: Climb The Big Easy, and move up and right at the 5th bolt

name: Fists of glory
description: P1:Climb up the right most crack in the three crack system, get behind large flake and traverse left to a semi spacious belay ledge and build anchor. Very very easy climbing the first pitch is simply to avoid the choss and rope drag. 5.5 P2:The fun climbing begins. Climb the corner crack which starts at small hands and slowly turns into fists of glory.

name: Fluffy Fly
description: Climb the tall face next to an obvious water groove.Â

name: Frigid Digit
description: Go to ledge, tram right, pull roof.

name: Hobo Station (Closer to the Edge)
description: Easier climbing leads to a stopper crux.

name: Hobos and Hand Grenades
description: Climb the obvious crack in the corner of hobo cave. Utilize really good hand jams and the occasional face hold till you reach the very fun, thin lie-back crux. Take advantage of three really good rests on your way up. Then make the final traverse to the anchors on "Animal Husbandry". With its height, good placements, and great jams, this thing has potential to be one of the best trad lines in the canyon. Just needs more action! Get on it!Â

name: Living on the Edge
description: Rightmost route.

name: Pull My Finger
description: Climb the arete

name: Toothless Bill Daniels
description: P1: same as fists of glory P2: a fun squeeze takes you to an easy mantle and then fun juggy liebacking. Big gear.

name: Y TY N
description: Moving right and around the corner from Hobo Cave, the first sport route you will find is Y TY N. Its short, but thuggy. Â Â

name: American Handgunner
description: An amazing climb using a wide variety of holds. Keep it together for the crux near the top!

name: Astrological Soul Train
description: Technical with hidden olds around the right corner.

name: Barbarians at the Gate
description: Back to back boulder problems on pockets lead into fun, long moves between good crimps. Surpisingly powerful and dynamic compared to other routes at railroad rock, especially if you happen to find many of the holds just out of reach.

name: Blue Velvet
description: It was a fine day when Rich and Rob decided to equip this amazing line.  Beautiful pockets up the center of the corridor wall.  Right of Where's My Bourbon.  Not to be missed.

name: Damn Yankees
description: Back to back cruxes down low lead to easier terrain above.

name: The Drifter
description: Route much like the others.

name: Ego Tripping
description: This route climbs the face behind the large tree in between "Electrocutioner" and "Into the Sun". Great face climbing on great holds. One of the more sustained 10a's at the falls, this one will test your patience if you're at your limit.     "The crux is pretty hard if you don't see it. I happened to see it the first time thus the 10a grade. Jack it and its definately harder. Sweet finish huh?"   -Jeff Frizzell (FA)

name: Electrocutioner
description: Climb arete/face just to the left of of "Ego Tripping".   Leftmost bolted route/closest to tracks on southwest face.    May be in the low 5.9 range?   Avoid power lines (or grab them for the crux of your life)!

name: Into the Sun (Aka Fragile Egos)
description: This is a really cool and reletively long pockety line.  With a neat undercling-y and pocket-y crux right near the top, it is really fun.  Maybe a little hard for the grade but uber cool.

name: Where's My Bourban
description: Goes up the rightward arching arete. 5 stars in the guidebook!

name: Wild at Heart
description: Nice movement to a crux 3/4 the way up. Classic.

name: Access Granted
description: Begin on the large block (same start as "IN"), but break off right.

name: Bottom Feeder
description: Fight you way to the to the slab at the start to find yourself on a technical slab, making use of pockets and the arete.

name: Butcher of Baghdad
description: A super technical climb that goes up the wall perpindicual to Slab Stick Comedy.  Way hard and way cool.

name: Cheap Fame
description: Climb up and eventually through a small gulley

name: Creeper
description: A totally cool crack in a right facing dihedral.

name: Feeding the Rat
description: Wide, offwidth, squeeze, grovelling fun!!!!

name: IN
description: Start on the large block and climb up the left leaning crack, then proceed to climb the face and arete.

name: Love Isn't Always On Time
description: Climb surprisingly fun offwidth/squeeze in the corner.  Jam in while you jam out to whatever song is stuck in your head at the time. A good warm-up for Feeding the Rat around the corner.    This was probably FA'ed sometime in the 80s, but I haven't found a record of it.  If you did, let me know and I'll update it.

name: Mother's Day Special
description: Fun slab/small pocket traverse. Avoid using jugs on 'Procrastination'.

name: Permission Denied
description: Climb the face between the tree on the left side, and the right arete.

name: Procrastination
description: The crux is the last move before the anchors.  Most of the hand and foot placements are on large iron flakes.

name: Project
description: A WAAAYYY hard overhung and seemingly featureless face near the arete on the lefthand side of the face.

name: Slab Stick Comedy
description: A really wild and, as the name implies, hard slab.  A wacky thumb mantel crux on often moss covered rock often proves interesting.

name: Slab Stick Dihedral
description: Nice looking dihedral.

name: Sweeper
description: It is the sweeping crack (get it?) with the same start as Creeper.  Start as Creeper, but cut right and ascend the sweeping slabby dihedral.

name: Top Of The Morning To You
description: Climb the Lighter Colored "White" face to the right of a gully that zig zags.Â

name: Vertical Finger Crack
description: Alternating right and left facing crack.    "5.9ish" in Eric Ulner's "Vertical Heartland".

name: Preliminary Exam
description: The bad is the decent.  ****The rap tree is dead and decayed.  *****

name: The Prospectus
description: Big holds, relatively long-ish moves, slightly overhanging, mossy/dirty finish.

name: Illinois State
description: Crack formation in an inside corner shaped like like the state. Ascend where the Mississippi River would be.

name: Crybaby club
description: First route right of the Minstrel

name: Cut Throat
description: Pocket climbing, to a bulge crux. Slabish ending.

name: Deep Throat
description: Pulling the overhang is entertaining.

name: Earthbound Misfit
description: Easy pocket climbing, leads to a crux pulling the bulge, and ends on a stint of slab.

name: Group Therapy
description: Overhanging jug haul. A hold broke off the original line, increasing the difficulty. Keep an eye out for the no hands rest ~2/3 of the way up!

name: King's Jester
description: Start on the big crack 10 feet further left of The Walrus.  Go up through the vertical seam.  Bottom can protect with wedges if you need them.     Variation 5.10c: Stay a few feet right of the 2nd clip.

name: Lone Star
description: Short but good, beginner-friendly for sure. Start at the bottom, climb to the top. Use the holds.

name: The Minstrel
description: Start to the right of chemney about 6ft, after the last bolt there is a gear placement in a pocket, a #3 tri-cam , if you need it, may have been retro bolted,

name: Needs A Name
description: Climb the face near the hanging pine

name: Psychotherapy
description: Somewhat sustained difficulty. Hard stuff seemed to be in the middle.

name: Shock Therapy
description: Low crux. One move wonder. Fun first clip.

name: Sore Throat
description: Another classic line at the Gallery, start on easy terrain and move through several cruxes up higher.

name: Squirrel House Crack
description: Overhung crack to the left of Group Therapy.  When crack ends, climb to the left or right (your choice) and top out on either Group Therapy or King's Jester.

name: The Walrus
description: Sustained high quality route, makes a great warm-up.  Crux is somewhat height-dependent and involves surmounting the first bulge about half way up. Slab top out.

name: Yuppie with a Gun
description: Interesting climbing, different than most of the routes at the Gallery. The anchor is set unnecessarily far back up a lichen covered slab, but one could easily use "The Walrus" anchor just to the left before the low-angle slab.

name: The Bad
description: Middle of the 10's on the west side.

name: Energizer
description: Climb just left of the arete on steepness.

name: The Good
description: The left of three 10's on the west side of the boulder.

name: Touch My Shelf
description: More steep goodness.

name: The Ugly
description: A short route on the west side.

name: What John Payne Doesn't Know
description: Super fun, technical, bouldery start using the huge roof feature directly below the first bolt. Navigate the juggy tufa into a couple shallow holds on your way to the huge rail. Easy pocket and hueco climbing diagonally out right to the anchors.    Couldn't find this in any guidebooks or in the memory of local John Paine. Let me know if you know anything about it.

name: Ainât No Sunshine
description: Difficult moves off of thin holds, monos, and bad slopers on great stone = one difficult route!

name: Applejack Crack
description: From behind the large tree, follow the thin crack upward until it widens into a large water groove off width/chimney at about 15 feet. Follow to the top.

name: Areteouffee
description: More challenging than it looks!

name: Big Dog
description: Climb up to the depression near bolt 3. Be ready for hard moves

name: Bill & Teeâs Excellent Adventure
description: Climb up the arete to the right.

name: Buckets of Jam
description: A bouldery start will get you onto the plates that  line the face, but you're not out of the bucket yet. Alternate jug hauling the face and thrutching in the wide crack until you come out to the ledge, where you can take a seat and consider your next move.     The anchor/descent is not ideal. You could scramble up the gully and try to find a tree to belay from, but I'm not sure what is available and getting down will be more of a chore. You can also traverse the ledge to the shiny new anchors two routes over and belay from there, but your follower might not be thrilled about the traverse.    Awkward route, but buckets of fun if you're into that kind of thing.

name: Corporal Punishent
description: Please note, this is a mixed line that you must rappell into from the top.Â

name: Extinguisher
description: 100 feet left of Ragin' Cajun, stay inside broken block hallway. Starts in a roof with a large, flat flake. 5 QD to the first fixed anchor. Variation 5.13a. Two more QD left to the other fixed anchor. F/A Chris Schmick 2001 From "Vertical Heartland" 3rd edition by Eric Ulner

name: Ice Harvest
description: Climb using small crips to reach the top.

name: Manhatten Project
description: Begins with a difficult boulder problem, which leads to hard sustained climbing and a blockbuster finish to the chains. To get full points for this route, avoid using the wall on the right. Contrived, I know.

name: Orion
description: Beginning off the small boulder, pull through some tricky moves and the climbing get easier the higher you climb.

name: Rajunâ Cajun
description: Technical powerful climb.

name: Ridin' Cowgirls
description: A thought provoking and challenging climb for the grade on sculpted holds.  Don't let the top fool you!

name: The Shootist
description: Similar to Corporal Punishment, this too you will need to rappel in from the top.Â

name: Stalking Horse
description: A great looking almost blank face that have never been sent. Good Luck

name: Stray Dog
description: An odd route that definitely "strays" from the bolt line. The beginning is intentionally bolted to force a face move that is probably the crux of the climb but then the climb moves into the chimney for 2 bolts. Up higher there is a great looking, thin section of wall that is appealing but the path of least resistance climbs the dirty rock to the left.

name: The Dagger
description: This is a former trad route that has since been bolted. It's a slab climb typical of jackson Falls, although with more features than you might expect. A little sketchy for the new leader, stick clip recommended in this case. Once established on the route, the first three bolts are pretty easy to clip. Keep moving right and you might need your belayer to describe the feet. Once you establish moving upward, it only gets easier to the top.

name: Dos Hombres
description: About 30 feet right of "The Reckoning", easy moves up to a high block/ledge then climb the arete by its right side.

name: Eminent Domain
description: Starts on the slab between Viking Blood and The Flail.  A couple bolts of interesting slab climbing, followed by 3 bolts of business as the wall turns vertical to slightly overhanging toward the top.  Don't fall off the heartbreaker lurch to the chains!    The feet are pretty bad on this route.  You'd best pick a chilly day to ensure your rubber sticks! Also come with good skin, as there's a razor crimp at bolt 4.

name: The Flail
description: Start over the low roof and climb the face to anchors under the right of the high roof.

name: If I Could Fly
description: In the middle of the east wall, 15 feet right of Void Warrior. Initially, at rainy day 2002, Me and my friend from Poland, Tomasz Samitowski start bolting from the ground. We put 2 bolts. I equiped entire route 5 years later, after successful top rope attempt by my son Maciek. At this time I was not able even repeat first crux move.

name: The Reckoning
description: Start in a smooth, tiny right-facing corner then go up and left.  About 25 feet right of "Wrecking Ball", and just at the hallway entrance, its the leftward angling sport route.

name: Solace
description: Long moves and some tricky climbing on pockets.   Possible climb above the anchor to the top of the tower. Established as solace, when I was not able to repeat  crux moves on my then 5 years old project on left.

name: Viking Blood
description: Start 12 feet right of the arete and go straight up the face.

name: Void Warrior
description: Start on the boulder and climb over the right of the low roof.

name: Wrecking Ball
description: Climb the overhanging prow of the tower, big dyno.

name: Beaver Bones
description: Gear climb the left-facing dihedral.

name: The Bolted One
description: Gear climb the right-facing flake/crack in the corner.

name: Bursting Out
description: Start 6 feet right of the alcove/chimney. Climb through the beginning bulged to gain the face, which is one of the most technical at Jackson. Pull onto the roof and get ready to crank. This climb is a great mix of balance and power, thin crimps and slopers, with a little spice to top things off.Â

name: East of East St. Louis
description: Climb in the middle of the face.  Vertical, then steep.

name: Flight of the Dodo
description: Was an oldÂ JF project. Technical and bouldery start up a sloping seam followed by a good rest. Culminates in a hard deadpoint over a bulge from a bad pinch and a mono iron-jib.

name: King Snake
description: A project given 5 stars in the guidebook, this has been sent since then. "Beautiful pockets leading to a steep slab top out.

name: The Off-Width Exam
description: No text - use the 'Improve This Page' link to add something useful!

name: The Sophomore
description: Start 15 feet left of the small corner and climb up to the right of the high bulge.

name: Splinter Faction
description: Before entering the hallway, climb up and right on the left side of the steep face.

name: Thai Chi Warrior
description: The crux on this one is low to the ground. Donât get too comfortable after the crux though, lack of feet makes it easy to punt before making it to the chains!

name: Tons of Fun
description: Climb up to a right-facing flake then the face and the left side of the bulge.  Lives up to it's namesake....

name: Unknown  2
description: No text - use the 'Improve This Page' link to add something useful!

name: DSB
description: A great line on sculpted holds. No individual move is that hard, but the pump will get you if you're not careful!

name: Dynasty
description: A serious endurance haul. Stacked boulder problems with lack of tests makes this one real hard!

name: Emperor of the North
description: Bouldery down low with great pocket climbing.

name: Empress of the South
description: Climb up the blunt arete.

name: Flaire
description: Follow the flairing crack above the dihedral.

name: Flappin' Jack
description: A great route on the left side of the wall. Climb through a short steep section to a puzzling crux, to a lower angle section leading to a final mantle at the chains. In other words, use the holds go up.

name: Hydraulic Hyena
description: Pull some serious moves on poor holds.

name: Mighty Mouse
description: Beginning just right of the tree, climb the line up the middle of the face that is surrounded by huecos.

name: Mouse in Your Pants
description: The only drawback to this route is that it's short. Other than that its varied and challenging. Don't let the guidebook description deter you, the tops not really bad at all even if there is moss up there its still totally climbable.

name: The Munchkin
description: Climb the route on the Munchkin Boulder found in the hallway corridor.

name: Open Project
description: This project shares the start with DSB and Flaire, but moves left. Please note it is partially bolted.Â

name: Russia
description: Tough lock off to start and hidden holds near the top. Are you a bolshevik?

name: That's What She Said
description: A partially bolted route.

name: Tin Man
description: Climb the short cliff face just right of the crack system.

name: The Munchkin
description: On the high point of the boulder inside the hallway.

name: Archangel
description: Lower crux with fun moves all through the climb.  A little slabby and balancy as well.  Really fun moves pulling the roof at the end to clip anchors.

name: BBD
description: Direct start to Blood Beets. Pull hard through an initial boulder problem to a standing rest. Tackle a precision pockets section, then go straight into the coolest part of the route; 2 bulges of requiring some sort of wizardry to navigate. Ahhhhmazing!

name: Blood Beets
description: Climb the not so easy start on Easy Gully. Gently reach right to clip the first bolt. Two back to back crux sections await you. Crank through the first and desperatly balance through the second.

name: Deetle Dumps
description: Climb the iron-plated line.

name: Easy Gully
description: The crux is the start of the route. This is a good litle route. A lot of fun moves can be found in the gully. You can stem, chimeny, or just smear your way up.

name: Ebee
description: This route is located 10 feet right of The Meanest Flower.

name: Expressions
description: Climb up the red colored smear on the wall.Â

name: Heading Skills Or Hospital Bills
description: Climb the crackÂ

name: Hunters Arrow
description: This is a fun route especially on lead. The guide book says that it is a 5.10a but I would give it a 5.9 just because the main face is mostly slab with great stances and plenty of places to rest. Also I climbed this when the rock was wet inside the crack and it was still an easy climb for me. The crux is at the very top when you have to pull around and behind the prominent point.   The only bad thing about the route is that rope drag is almost unavoidable especially if you're setting a TR.

name: Ketex
description: Boulder up to a big ledge (currently the crux by a long shot because it is super mossy). Once there, enjoy fun, sequential and sometimes improbable technical climbing to the top. A good and varied route for sure.

name: Kryptonite
description: Climb the bulging, three part roof network.Â

name: The Meanest Flower
description: Cool line with a low crux and the another small one after the last bolt.

name: My Head is Broke
description: I thought this was a really great, very sustained technical climb. Epic shallow-stemming crux, sequential foot traverse. Small holds, but you don't have to pull super hard because the rock is vertical to less-than-vertical. Awesome. Climbs more like a Smith Rock 12a than most Jackson routes.

name: No Dancers
description: Climb up and through a short overhang (fun!), past 2 bolts (crux at second bolt). After surmounting the bulge, scramble up a low 5th class crack system, with a maybe 5.8 mossy crux getting up to the anchor (Step left to share anchor with Ebee).

name: No Dogs Allowed
description: Low crux to iron flakes at the top.

name: Pete's Lead
description: Easy well-protected lead. The crux is mid-way up where the crack widens and the flake becomes bulbous making it tough to lie back.  The crux has a couple of vertical mail slot pockets on the left face that are easy to miss.  Above the crux it becomes an easy scramble to the finish where a horizontal crack takes gear to protect on the short traverse right to the anchors for the sport route, Smidgin.

name: The Raconteur
description: The hardest tradÂ line in the canyon. Climb the thin crack till it's turns into a wide crack then top out.

name: Smidgin
description: Slab route.

name: Sunflower
description: Interesting moves through the first three bolts and then a little run out to the fourth bolt.

name: Tina's Soul Food Kitchen
description: This is a slab route that looks much easier from the ground.  The book Vertical Heartland has it listed as a 5.7, so I kept the rating.  It felt closer to a 5.9 to me.

name: The Vow
description: Open book gully.  Harder than it looks...

name: Daddy's big snake/Anaconda traverse
description: Traverse along the crack parallel to the ground till you reach the jug rail on Who Let the Snakes Out, keep going on the rail till you reach another bolt on the 12c, then clip the anchors.

name: Feathered Serpent
description: Pull a few moves to get under the roof, set up for the huge crux throw, pull a couple more tough moves out the roof, then fight the pump at the sloper finish before the chains.

name: Goin Rogue
description: V5/6 problem to easier climbing

name: Here Come the Snakes
description: Big holds...big moves...bigger fun.

name: Inner Pitbull
description: WOW! This one is hard. Moderate climbing to the third bolt takes you to a difficult boulder problem with a sloper from your nightmares.

name: Umbrella Girls
description: Short, overhung route. Finishes at the scooped out dish just right of snakes roof.

name: Who Let the Snakes Out
description: Climb up to the juggy rail.  Traverse to the right on said rail.  Clip chains.

name: Discovering Sin
description: Start a few feet to the right of the first bolt. Climb up using decent pockets until you reach a blank section. Rest up, grab the jug, throw big and try to finish.

name: Fine Nine
description: Climb up a surprisingly engaging slab with committing crux moves up higher that can be baffling for some at first.

name: Hidden Treasures
description: One of the cleanest lines around. Great "first" 12 interesting moves protected well where needed.

name: Lefty Crack
description: Fun and safe little 5.7 crack that is good for the new trad leader. Very safe stances, although the gear can be a little tricky. From lovely arete, go around to the left and ascend the obvious left-leaning crack at about a 45 degree angle. It's jug hauling near a crack feature; no jamming required.

name: Lithuanian Chimney
description: Fun chimney route.

name: Lost Innocence
description: No text - use the 'Improve This Page' link to add something useful!

name: Lovely Arete
description: Where Lovely Tower and the Wave Wall form the Lovely Hallway, this is the obvious arete. A bouldery start to the first bolt leads to the meat. Fun stuff.

name: Rain Dog
description: Long pulls on pretty good holds.

name: Split Decision
description: Follow the line of 3 bolts just the left of Fine Nine. The route goes straight up the slab with the help from committing smearing, quartz pebbles, and faint pockets.

name: Velvet Green
description: A great pockety line with the crux below the last bolt...too bad it's so short.

name: Blue Spark
description: water gooves,flakes

name: Cosmic Banditos
description: This is a tough one that only gets harder.Â

name: D-Man
description: Hardest bolted line on the face, but a fun route that involves some interesting climbing and will have you reaching deep into your bag of tricks.

name: The Garden Route
description: Its the high angle slab with a thin start up to good knobs and iron flakes.

name: Heavy Horses
description: Another pocket puller. Donât worry, there are holds somewhere in the moss!

name: Lovinâ the Rain
description: Climb up the zig-zagging crack. The start is pretty cruiser on good holds until the second bolt. From here do your best to figure out how to make it to the top!

name: Marley's Nose Variation
description: Start on the arete from the ground down left then pull on to the face at the first bolt.

name: Master Marley
description: The crux is the first moves up to the first bolt. A fall here is quite dangerous if you swing off to the left. Easily break ankle here. (stick clip useful.)

name: Rattler
description: Crux that works up a crack system involving some interesting and fun footwork right at the first bolt.

name: Songs from the Wood
description: Start on impossibly slick feet with small crimps for hands, move up to first bolt. Past this the route is 5.7/5.8 or easier.     If you stick clip the first bolt and pull up, it would be 5.7 A0 and a great route for beginners!

name: Storm Watch
description: Pull on some small pockets to the top.

name: Suit and Tie
description: Start in the obviously chalked up inner corner. Follow the thin crack in the boulder up and to the left. Top out    This guy is a little dirty, so bring a brush.

name: Through the Smoke
description: water grooves to knobs and jugs

name: Agent Orange
description: Moderate climbing leads to a distinct crux, with a delicate slab to finish the route off.

name: Amoeba Brains
description: Diffucult bouldery start leads to more moderate climbing up the arete.  After 3rd bolt exit arete to right and finish on slab top-out.

name: Angry Child
description: This ones hard the whole way!

name: Beastie
description: Climb the off width that is protected by bolts. Not as easy as it looks

name: Cro-Magnon Warrior
description: Very obvious line in the middle of the wall.  Follow a seam using power liebacking.  The 1st sport route at the falls.  Mega classic.

name: Cyber Sex
description: This is the route close to the trail that is protected by "eye bolts". Climb through good holds and save some juice for the end.

name: Dancing Bear
description: Climb the face that bulges

name: Diamonds And Rust
description: Climb the shorter, dark colored face.Â

name: Digital Direct
description: Wow this one is thin, so you better be on your crimp game! Begin by negotiating your way through thin holds, until they get slightly better. At the last bolt you'll run into what looks like a blank section covered in moss. Keep your eyes out for the mono, it's key to get to the anchors.

name: Fancy Feet
description: Get out your dancing shoes for this trickster.  Good fun.

name: Goblin Girl
description: Step up the mossy slab to reach the first bolt. Pull the bluge and find a good stance to clip the 2nd bolt. High step and friction your way to the top.

name: Keepers of the Skill
description: Cool looking lieback.

name: L.A. Woman
description: Lieback the crack to the good face holds on the right.  Top out straight up.

name: Ladies' Choice
description: Arching wide crack just right of L.A. Woman.  Might be full of muck.

name: Little Johnny Jewel
description: A few tough, thin reaches down low leads to excellent, thoughtful climbing above on positive flakes.

name: Morning Beers
description: A beautiful sweeping dihedral crack on the dark bands of rock typical of the first Doors wall headed towards the N. Falls.   Cruiser with an exciting roof finish to the anchors!   If you see this is dry then climb it.

name: No Brains
description: Climb up the pebbly pocketed face. Holds are pretty painful!

name: Snap Dragon
description: Climb up the rainbow colored slab until you get the head wall. Take a breath before you break into an extremely difficult boulder problem with a one hand dyno to a sloper. It doesnât end there, make sure you stay on your toes till youâre clipping the chains at the top.

name: Southern Belle
description: This is the possible looking, extremely hard, bolted arete seam

name: The Stain
description: A fun route when it isnt wet or mossy.

name: The Twist
description: Begins as a jug haul to the high first bolt. Survive some thin slab to reach the chicken heads and a good ledge at the anchor.

name: Bug Meat
description: Weird start. bulgy. would be a better route if it wasn't so dirty.

name: Huecool
description: Crux is the first move. Fun climb but way too short.

name: Hydra
description: Hydra is a nice short moderately bouldery line with three bolts, that goes up and moves slightly diagonally right.

name: Lovin' Lizards
description: This is the spot where the fixed line used to be. It has since been bolted as a sport route. A great way to get out of the canyon at the end of the day.

name: On Thin Ice
description: Very precarious climbing through shallow pockets.Â

name: Puff
description: Third route to the right of the pool, with a bulge at the top.  First bolt is a good 15 feet off of the ground.

name: Temporary Escape
description: This is the second bolted line left of the corner from the hand line. A very weird start leads up to a bulge. Pulling the bulge ends up easier than it looks, working the slopers above is not.

name: Working Man Blues
description: Good, short sport route

name: Breakfast Club
description: The route between Wizards Hat and Eat Dirt. This one will need some cleaning before a send attempt

name: Brown Recluse
description: Another Frizzell technical masterpiece.  Finishes in between two high water grooves

name: Deception
description: Climb the dihedral crack next to the low roof.

name: Eat Dirt
description: This widish crack flares somewhat and is usually fairly dirty and rarely done.  It's really not as bad as that description sounds though!

name: Femme Fatale
description: Be patient with this one, it will be slow going on not so confidence inspiring holds. Slowly pull your way up a water groove

name: Mud Pie
description: Good slabby/vertical sport route worth doing as you work down to the Gallery

name: Retrospect
description: This project is the face climb between the two cracks

name: Settled Controversy
description: Ascend the lieback flake with the horn on top.  Top out on right.

name: Skinny Dipper
description: Thought provoking start. Move up and a little right on the Face.

name: Spring Animation
description: Initially lead on 3 bolts, rated 5.11c. 2 bolts added + anchor shared with Deception.

name: Stand & Deliver
description: A super fun sport route up the flaring gully.  Crux comes at 2/3 height and it really makes you stand and deliver!

name: Star Power
description: Climb the dark red face using everything you can find

name: Suspended Animation
description: Start climbing below and to the right of the crack in the middle of the wall.

name: T & A
description: The route that starts above a bolder near a fallen tree

name: What's the Deal with Tim?
description: Bouldery start leads to 5.10ish climbing above

name: Wizard's Hat
description: Crack in the back of an overhanging symmetrical dihedral.  Looks like a wizard's hat.

name: Access Denied
description: It is recommended to stick clip the first bolt. Climb up and through a left leaning edge feature.Â

name: Big Brother
description: Choss but unique for jackson

name: Chuck-O-Rama
description: Climb the face to the left of the Arete.Â

name: Creep Show
description: This is a fun slabby route in the Manky Alcove.  A bit of balance is helpful.

name: Essence of Manky
description: Stem up the back of the alcove until your legs can't stretch anymore and switch to the left side to lie back the crack to the anchors.  Fun route but too short.

name: Hungry Wolf
description: Fingery, vertical sport route that is short and sweet

name: Slug Man
description: This is the face/slab route on the left.  Pull a move, stand on ledge x3

name: Crab Cakes
description: Pull pockets up left to the blunt arete. Pinch and roll right to sidepulls then deadpoint left to gain the shelf. Hand traverse right then pull the roof.Move up left to the anchors. It's still dirty but super fun! Feel free to brush a little  on the way down from your flash.

name: Dolphin Friendly
description: Face climb on nice holds. Pull the roof

name: Fred & Wilma
description: Climb this cliff line route that is broken up into 2 separate tiers.Â

name: Jimmy Gillespie
description: Unknown

name: Needs A Name
description: Start on the detached boulder to the right then traverse left on slopers to gain the roof. Power through the roof using jugs and heel hooks, then mantle and clip the chains

name: Tree Hugger
description: Climb the 4 bolt route

name: Den of Thieves
description: Low crux passing the first bolt. Relentless to tricky finish.

name: End of the Cluster
description: Utilize fingerlocks and good face holds; its more fun than it looks from the ground.

name: Fat and Sassy
description: Hop up to ledge to for the first bolt. Then either follow the leftward leaning crack with some underclings or move slightly left and use a combination of the face the crack.

name: Flash
description: 5.10 a/b Its the first sport route, just right of "Spinkles". 3 QD + anchor. From "Vertical Heartland" 3rd edition by Eric Ulner

name: Lightning
description: Pull up onto the route using good jugs until about the second bolt, where the route transitions into crimps. The crux is moving out right and to clip the anchors. After a few falls, I found it best to clip whlie right hand is on the lower right undercling with high feet, instead of trying to use the higher hold on the left.

name: Raise The Roof
description: This is the only route of Rainy Day Roof that goes all the way to the top.Â

name: Silver Lining
description: A liitle bit techy at the crux from 2 to 3. A bit pumpy to finish.     The grade is a guess please add your opinion

name: Sprinkles
description: A short but decent crack that can be protected strictly by nuts.  It goes up and right.

name: Sweet Leaf
description: Crux going from 1 to 2. Nice holds to a trickly finish.

name: Thunder
description: no visible anchors

name: Zapped
description: Basically a highball boulder problem, but a really fun boulder problem. Lots of good holds with big reaches in between. Pull hard and fast and you're gonna have a good time.

name: Automatic Damnation
description: Start with a little bit of technical climbing till you get to the second bolt. Proceed on overhanging jugs till you get to the lard flake. Use a combination of bad smears and good handholds to get to the roof crack.

name: Industry
description: Short and bouldery.  May be easier?

name: Optical Conclusion
description: A big underclung feature helps identify this route. It is big and long. Have fun

name: Pulse
description: Power through the low section until you get to the last bolt. Be ready to pull on some heinous crimps for the finish!

name: Addiction
description: Begin on OCD and upon reaching the 5th bolt, continue straight up to the anchor. Route is often wet, if dry, you will not be disappointed.

name: Aggro-Sheen
description: Climb the slight arete feature until the horizontal break. Cut left and continue up to the anchor.

name: Aggro-Sheen Direct
description: Begin on Aggro-Sheen, but at the horizontal break, continue straight up.

name: The Diggler
description: Climb the rightward leaning crack protecting when necessary working towards the bolts to reach the anchor.

name: Hearty Boys Crack
description: Climb the zig zagging crack while protecting when necessary.

name: Iniquity
description: Climb the face to work your way through a bulge, continue through a slab to reach the top. Large Eye Bolts mark this route.

name: OCD
description: Climb up a steep face and upon reaching the 5th bolt, cut left to work towards the anchor. (Obsessive Climbing Disorder)

name: Unknown
description: Follow the bolts as you climb through a bulge to eventually gain purchase on a slab. continue to the anchor from here.

name: Watch Dog
description: Begin on top of the boulder and carefully climb up the face using small holds.

name: The Carpenter
description: The rightmost route on the Detox wall, start as for The Farmer but continue up the ramp for another 10 feet to a lieback crack. Continue up the crack and finish on edges.

name: Cocktail Generation
description: Straight up then move left into a cool span move. Gain the break then move slightly up and right to pull the overlap on edges. Finish up and left.

name: Cocktail Tribe
description: Cocktail Generation with Elders finish

name: Coral Crack
description: The large crack 20 feet right of Devil's Lake Dreams.

name: Cranial Implosion
description: Climbs up on the short overhanging face.

name: Detox Mountain
description: A total classic in the Jackson Falls area and the midwest for that matter.  A tendon friendly pocket pulling extravaganza.

name: Devil's Lake Dreams
description: Splitter hand to off-fist crack leads to some fun offwidth twists, leads to some face climbing.  A couple rest ledges thrown in makes this climb a blast and a half, if you've got guts.

name: Elders of the Tribe
description: A gnarly climb and a super fun one to boot.  Standard J Falls sandstone pockets and crimps.

name: The Farmer
description: Start low by Detox and move up line of bolts to the right.  Gets interesting after the layback crack.

name: Kaya
description: Short line that does not receive great reviews

name: Ode To Mary Joe
description: This is the cool looking Arete climb to the right of Detox Mountainâs main routes. It does not receive enough traffic

name: Better Eat Your Weedies
description: Looks easier then it is. Save some strength for the top

name: Captain Crunch
description: A way cool line up the middle of Pricker Peak.  Follow the line to the bulge.  Pull that, then finish up.

name: Cheerio Bowl
description: Climb through the first three bolts (crux) to the prow like feature.  Then take a good rest and head left to the face, up the arete and then cut right and up to the finish.  A pumpy finish to the chains.

name: Froot Loops
description: Start on big easy stuff, up to first bolt. Â Some awkward, hard face climbing, with high steps and thin holds to pull hard on, and scary slopers for the final pull to the top.

name: Honey Nut Girl
description: A nice line, bit more powerful than its neighbor Captain Crunch.

name: Lucky Charms
description: Crux is at the third bolt. Kinda of run out past it but it's pretty easy climbing.

name: Molatov Cocktail
description: Big holds on slightly overhung wall. Good route to get your final Red Point warm up pump on.

name: Power Pump
description: Beginning above a two foot boulder, climb through an obvious lieback up and left

name: Raisin Bran
description: Shared anchor with Lucky Charms

name: Feed Me
description: Great holds lead to a tricky crux.Â

name: The Juggler
description: This is a mixed line that has 5 bolts to help protect the face. Youâll need some gear for the dihedral seam at the top.Â

name: Lothlorien
description: First 20 feet are vertical to a slight balancey crux then the angle easies slightly along with the difficulty.

name: The Monument
description: Another fine route among the many quality lines of the Hidden Peaks area. Climb the middle of the face (left of Lothlorien and the tall tree close to the face). A tall first bolt gives you an idea of the spacing.

name: Naked Blade
description: A wicked fun mixed route on the arete of the Monument.  Head up the arete to a really good rest on a ledge, a brown tricam has a bomber placement here.  Then sport up to the finish.

name: The Road To Serfdom
description: Two moves of fragile rock lead to pockets in excellent rock. Fight hard direct or come in from the left with style. Three sections of interesting climbing with slight breaks in between. You may find it pumpy for the angle.

name: Stubborn Swede
description: One of the best routes of the grade at Jackson

name: A Year with You
description: Adventurous meandering route with all kinds of climbing moves, roof crack, offwidth, squeeze, face, anchor on tree.  Extend to prevent rope drag.

name: Coup D'etat
description: V6/7 to easier climbing above

name: Miserable
description: Link "Misery" into "Coup de'etat"

name: Misery
description: Climb up the manky overhang using a variety of sandy pinches. Very thuggy!

name: Obed Simulater C.
description: Start by climbing up Misery, but link into Obed Simulater B. instead of clipping the chains.

name: Obed Simulator B.
description: Start on Coup, but continue left through the roof.

name: Roots
description: Enter a non typical sport route for the canyon. Â Adventure up the wide crack feature using more than your average sport climbing technique. Â An ode to good fun on good rock for those who grew up/fell in love with climbing in Illinois and will never forget their roots.

name: Bubbling Crude
description: Engaging climbing throughout, chains are slightly to the right of the rest of the climb. Crux is probably clipping the chains, I traversed over and clipped while still below the bulge, but it also looks like you could pull over and then traverse to the anchors, although that also seems a little strange.

name: Court House
description: Climb up an easy section to get to the business. Climb up and over a couple of bulges with good clipping stances, and push through the crux above the final bolt.  Fun, and very well protected!

name: Dances With Sharks
description: Boulder up to the 2nd bolt.  Wrestle your way around the fin and fight to the anchors. Unique movement for the Falls!  Grade is a guess, please add your opinion. First TR ascent: Jeff Frizzell

name: Double Knot Spy
description: Fun and juggy laybacking and stemming with good gear. Crux is probably 1/3 the way up.

name: Gangster of Love
description: Variation on "Space Cowboy", continue left to the separate anchor. 8 QD + anchor. From "Vertical Heartland" 3rd edition by Eric Ulner

name: Gully Gee Whiz
description: There is a water dike in the middle of this route.  Pull slopers, pinches, side pulls, pockets, and under-clings.  Boulder to gain the lower bulge, then enter the gully, use your shoulders.  At the top of the gully, come out on the face and pick the pockets on the first roof up to the giant fin.

name: I Be Lichen' It
description: Sustained overhanging route.  Tough finish to the anchors.

name: Katie Did
description: Good feet, a few bulges to get over.  Pinches, heucos and jugs.  Bolts nicely spaced.

name: Lindapalooza
description: The route at the entrance to the corridor.Â

name: Lying Back with Ellie Mae
description: Lieback the juggy lip on the left side of this crack, don't forget to look for good feet on the left for rests. Sustained and continuous, a fun natural feature to climb.

name: Monkey Shower
description: Bulge between 2nd and 3rd clips is the crux.  Pinches, heuco's and jugs.  A little overhanging for 1/2 of route, transitions to slab.

name: Possum Grits
description: Start on the bulgy start. Good rest just by the first bolt, nice safe start. The trick is finding the underclings throughout. Really good 5.9 on bomber sandstone. Good jugs at the top. Various beta to get from the last bolt to the anchor. Pick your adventure!

name: Space Cowboy
description: About 30 feet past the S.S. Minnow, it starts just right of the big, overhung dihedral. Cross the crack after the second clip and face climb through the bulge to the top. 8 QD + anchor. From "Vertical Heartland" 3rd edition by Eric Ulner

name: Spank You Very Much
description: Good pockets and jugs to clip from.  A few bulges with good feet.  Slab after last hanger to anchors.  Move right for good feet and a hand jam.

name: Uncle Albert Plays The Blues
description: Itâs the route down the corridor from Lindapalooza on the left side of the cliffline

name: Whee Doggies!
description: A pockety line starting from up on the ledge. This area is rarely trafficked but the holds stay nice and clean. Good route for the young leader. Also, a nice ledge up top to teach cleaning anchors. It's just near a 5.9 and past several other 5.9s. A very good beginner area.     The hardest moves are near the bottom, then move up and left for jugs.

name: You Can't Take the Sky From Me
description: In a battle between claustrophobia and acres of air below you, this climb forces you to fight for any shred of sky you can.  20ft of upside-down, offwidth hell leads to an mild finger traverse, and then 40ft of your standard chimney (lil' dirty, lil' runnout, lil' fun).

name: Salty Dog
description: A fairly easy 10a climb for the area, definitely recommended for people new to the grade. Generally good holds on good rock.

name: Skipper
description: Start Left of a big tree on easy terrain, follow fun mega-jugs along a traverse for 3 or 4 bolts, then up the face to the shiny new chain anchor. Good times! Crux is probably somewhere on the face. Listed as 10b in the Daneshyar guide, but its probably easier than that. Significantly easier than three hour tour.

name: Swabbe
description: Continuous technical climbing, close to vertical but not overhanging. Different in character than a lot of Jackson routes.

name: Three Hour Tour
description: North side of block. Start on boulders next to "Swabbe" and climb left toward the prow and arching toward the summit. The last (fifth) bolt you see on the main face is the last bolt on the route, but the terrain above is really easy. After clipping this bolt the route moves left and finishes up the left (low angle and highly featured) side of the headwall.

name: Benny Hill
description: Power slab to better holds through the bulge

name: Brief Respite
description: Crux shortly after 2nd bolt.    Try to avoid the temptation of the iron flakes to the left midway up!

name: Condor
description: A decievingly easy start leads to hard face climbing.

name: Dave Smokes
description: Climb the crack

name: Disco Fever
description: Starts out slaby with long reaches to vertical terrain with few bad options for holds. Power through the defined crux about half way, but keep your cool for the next few bolts, it's very possible to fall after the crux.

name: Ever Ready Betty
description: More to it than meets the eye. Safe, mental, and entertaining. Be strong grasshopper.

name: Flower Child
description: Also known as Cowgirls in The Sand. Start on Groovy Marcia move right and follow the buttress left of Disco Fever.

name: Groovy Marcia!
description: A black water runnel to the left of Lasso the Vulture.  Strat with an awkward mantel to 5.9 slabby open book goodmness.

name: Kill Bill
description: A pretty cool slab up the middle of the face.  The last climb on this side of the canyon.

name: Land of Nod
description: Brutish pull to start. Stick clip if you must. Angle left to the anchors. Safe with a precarious feel. Good rock/holds

name: Lasso the Vulture
description: This is definately one of my favorite route in the Falls.  A lowdown crux (between first and third bolts) follws to easier climbing up and to the left of the blank roof.  Follow the chimney (would you believe it) to the anchors.

name: Little Blue Pill
description: Ease up and the right under the two tiers then straight up.

name: Mad Hatter
description: Left angling groove then back right to the anchors

name: Mirror Man
description: Right of "Ever Ready Betty"    Low Crux. 10ish climbing to an upper mini-crux and the anchors. Well bolted.

name: Rocket Morton
description: Pinches, slopers, pockets, dimples, deadpoints, smears, side pulls, Improbable finish. It aint over til its over.   Sweet!

name: Southern Inquisition
description: Low bouldery crux with consistent climbing through the rest of the top section.

name: Thrill Jill
description: Techy little right leaning corner (sweet) to a bulge. I may have screwed the bolting up a little at the buldge. My applogies

name: Unknown
description: This route is not in the newest Jackson guidebook. Staying left of the decaying tree trunk, follow bolts through what looks to be bleak sections and work your way to the anchor.Â

name: URSA Minor
description: Difficult moves off pockets crux is mid way up.Â

name: [Redacted]
description: Crux passing the first bolt. Safe but mildly run out to the Anchors. Great stone in a beautiful red streak.

name: Cactus Wren
description: Shares first bolt with Road Runner

name: Cara Cara
description: Just right of Road Runner. Mildly overhanging start. Hard to see first bolt. Shares anchors with Road Runner

name: Cloud Shadow
description: Maroon water groove

name: Cowboys and Cross Dressers
description: Short & Sweet

name: Darwin's Theory
description: 1 move wonder

name: Front Porch Vista
description: Bigin by using the tree. Let guilt be your guide

name: Road Runner
description: Shares first bolt with Catus Wren and anchor set with Cara Cara

name: They Shoot Horses Don't They
description: Mildly over hanging on very good stone. Fun moves

name: Bad Hombre
description: Just right of High Lonesome; Just left of the waterfall.

name: Barbed Wire
description: just right of Buckaroo

name: Black Eyed Beauty
description: Start same as Poncho Via, Hand traverse to the firrst bolt on Three Amigos,pull onto the face and keep moving left past bolt 2, up left to 3, then straight up to the anchors.

name: Buckaroo
description: angles left hidden hold left

name: High Lonesone
description: Just right of Javelina

name: Horseshoe Canyon Simulator
description: Right most route on the wall

name: Javelina
description: Just right of Barbed Wire

name: Sierra Negro
description: No text - use the 'Improve This Page' link to add something useful!

name: Three Amigos
description: 25 feet right of the waterfall

name: Twisted Goat
description: Right leaning semi tube with pockets

name: Black Tie Affair
description: Pull through a balancy start then crimp your way p to three large pockets. Gather your energy, put on your best sending suit, and burst out right to an obvious flake.

name: Bow Tie and Billfold
description: A tough lock-off right off the ground leads to great climbing above. Keep your guard up until the last!

name: Cigars and Scotch
description: Follow the right side of the arete on good pockets and luxurious underclings

name: Gentlemen Prefer Nature Girls
description: To the right of Top Hat and Cane. Follow the short face to the burly roof moves. V5/ 12c.

name: Hardwood Haberdasher
description: Climb and powerful face on good pockets up to overhanging iron-flake jugs. Finish with a balancy mantle, guaranteed to keep you on your toes!

name: Krakendile
description: Start a little left and work a move using some positive, yet hidden holds. Pull the tricky move, and then cruise easier territory to gain the anchors.

name: Owl-Cat
description: Use large pockets to undercling your way to a pair of tricky moves to bring yourself to the anchors. Just like the Owl-Cat of legend this will keep you on your toes until the end!

name: Top Hat and Cane
description: Fun climbing on the roof on the back side of Top Hat Tower. A short face leads to a beefy roof with big moves on decent holds. Fight the pump and let your feet cut for a great finish!

name: Tux with Tails
description: Great pockets lead to some fun iron flakes. Waltz your feet up high and undercling the tails for the finish.

name: 3 Day Impression
description: Interesting face climbing to the right of an arete leads to a nice rest, where you cross to the other side of the arete and tackle several classic Jackson-style bulges.

name: [Redacted]
description: Slave Labor starts at the same point as "Carpal Tunnel" and "Workshop". Veer right after first clip.

name: Adios Amigos
description: Begin on the platform, climb up the beautiful Black and Tan face. Keep your eye out for the drilled mono.

name: Assembly Line
description: Two difficult, technical cruxes on razor crimps separated by a section of more moderate climbing. Not for those afraid of a little blood.

name: Balance of Power
description: Very tall aesthetic route, with great movement.

name: Better Late Than Never
description: Start the route off by pulling on a couple small pockets, and a hard lock off move/drive by. The climbing gets easier, but itâs not over till you clip the anchors.

name: Big Chaw
description: Hard to read finish

name: Canât Take the Funk
description: Climb up the pocketed arete that leads to a committing slab above.

name: Carpal Tunnel
description: Starts at the same point as "Slave Labor" and "Workshop". Take the middle line after the 2nd clip.

name: Chameleon
description: This route starts off running with a low crux. Continue up the face using what sandy holds you can find. Shares the same anchors as âSalamanderâ.

name: Circle in the Round
description: Low crux leads to sustained climbing.

name: Congo Spray
description: Same start as Zambezi. Cut left after the second bolt to climb Congo Spray. The crux is right at the third bolt.Â

name: Delirious
description: This route climbs up the arete on the right side of the wall, next to the chimney.

name: Drop of Reflection
description: A variation of the route âPool of Reflectionâ. Start around the corner to the right, and join in at the 4th bolt.

name: Duppy Conqueror
description: Climb up the golden streaked face.

name: Egyptian Conniption
description: A low sever crux leads to easier terrain above.Â

name: Essence of Power
description: Start by aiding your way to the first bolt. Once in place, pull a long move to the lip and proceed to pull on sloping holds to a hard dead point move to a jug. Finish on easier terrain afterwords.

name: Essence of Power Free
description: The freed start to the old aid start of EOP. Pull down hard onÂ a slightly crumbly, compression boulder problem at the start into EOP. End at single bolt anchor. A project continues up and right.

name: Fashionably Late
description: Very fun, slightly technical pockets up a vertical face to an over hanging jug finish

name: Float Trip
description: Start with a moderate boulder problem to get from the ground to the second bolt. The crux sequence is between the 3rd andÂ the 5th bolt.

name: Four Bettys
description: Pure jackson fun, sloppers and all!

name: Gecko
description: Climb up the pocketed face on the left side of the buttress.Â

name: Generator X
description: Pumpy.

name: Hoser
description: This one is a little bit easier than Poseur. Climb up the middle line. Crux is a litttle thuggy and near the middle of the climb.

name: Hubba Hubba
description: Fight through the low crux at the first bolt to gain the steep sustained face.

name: Jarredâs Route
description: An interesting start leads to the first roof. Spend some time to figure out how to get in position to pull the roof. Donât get comfortable! The climbing only gets harder for every bulge you pull.

name: Key Lime
description: Climb up the lime green streak near the gully.Â

name: Killer Chickens
description: Climb up the left-facing flake until it runs out. Then move right and over the bulge.

name: Last Gasp of Hope
description: Climb up the left angling crack until Iï¸t stops. Proceed to climb up the face.

name: My Generation
description: Climb the crack and either end at the anchors or top out through the right gully.

name: Mystical Season
description: Start standing on the boulder to start the juggy traverse. The jugs run out when you pull yourself onto the head wall.

name: The Nile
description: Tough climbing leads to a extremely severe crux. Iâve been told the crux sequence is about v10 alone. Luckily after the crux itâs gets significantly easier on he way to the chains.

name: Ooh La La
description: Shares the same start as âHubba Hubbaâ, but you break left and follow the red streak at the 4th bolt.

name: Pinocchio Theory
description: This ones a little thuggy, with a dynamic move for the crux. You end up linking up with Team Honda near the top.

name: Pool of Reflection
description: Start with an interesting vertical crux to a good rest before big moves and sustained climbing through overhanging rock to hero jugs. A 13a variation goes up the arete to the right, bypassing the beginning crux. Listed as the Pipe Dream Project in Vertical Heartland.

name: Poseur
description: Begin on the left Angelina crack, but cut right and follow the furthest right bolt line. The crux is between bolt 2 and 3. But itâs not over till you clip the chains.

name: Remove la Ropa
description: A neat boulder problem gets you to a steep roof. Move through the "Jackson Falls Jugs" in the roof to a deadpoint gaining the face and easier climbing to the anchors

name: Salemander
description: Climb up the sandy face. Donât get tricked into going the wrong direction!

name: Skink
description: Climb up the bulging face.

name: Spectator Sport
description: Climb up the pocketed face.Â

name: Tacoâs ATV Jamboree
description: This route is tricky! Keep your eyes peeled for hidden holds.

name: Team Honda
description: Start on small holds and move up the overhanging face with large holds and larger moves. Cruise the roof to the chains.

name: Traffic Jam
description: Enjoy your ride up the wall on good positive holds.

name: Trap Line
description: Seemingly impossible start leading up to some unique climbing on typical Jackson slab holds. Some may consider hard for the grade.

name: Victoriaâs Secret
description: This route climbs up the dark streak slab. Probably also pretty dirty!

name: Workshop
description: Starts at the same point as "Slave Labor" and "Carpal Tunnel". Stay with the left line.

name: XOXO
description: Great warm up for the harder routes in the area.  A little thin at the start and continuous.

name: Xterminator
description: Goes up the arete.

name: XXX
description: This route starts on the left main face of the X Block and goes up the arete for 2 bolts. Then head left to finish up XOXO

name: Zambezi
description: Start climbing up the water groove. Do some long pulls on pockets. Interesting crux matching and moving off a not so great hold. Climbing gets easier after crux.

name: Bagpiper
description: Start on two underclings. Work up through two finger pocket and sloped rail. Get to jug rail and finish by turning on to the slab to the right or left. Have fun!!

name: Berlier Problem
description: Start low, matched on flake, then move right to a juggy gaston, then pull up.

name: Body Karate
description: A powerful and beautiful roof compression problem. It starts with a couple of big throws, then some compression with tensiony, far away feet, and finishes with hero climbing on an awesome rail.    If you always wanted to climb The Vice, but don't climb v13 or can't get to Africa, this is your problem.   Arguably the best boulder problem in the canyon, and good enough that it stands out in the region.   Feels v9 to some body types.

name: Cold Fusion
description: Start on slopers, travers right on arÃªte then pull yourself over the lip.

name: Corner Crouch
description: Just go straight up that corner from a sit start.

name: David and Goliath
description: Start with left hand on a crimp side pull, right on lowest chalked ledge. Catch thumdercling, adjust and huck for the lip.

name: Footweiser, The King of Smears
description: Start with your left hand on undercling crimp, and your right hand undercling pinch. Establish feet, then catch crimp and finish.

name: Girlier Problem
description: Start low on flake (same start as Berlier Problem), move up left.

name: Hypoglycemia
description: Begin with a sit start under the the Body Karate boulder, throw to the lip and traverse right and finish on Body Karate.

name: No Rest for the Weary
description: A fun 5 move problem that starts on the upper portion of the rail. Starts on two crimps with the left foot pasted on the lower rail and the right foot heel hooked on the side of the boulder. Reach high left for good crimp. Switch feet onto the rail. Reach out right for sloper on right corner of the boulder. Heel hook up high left by left hand. Find right hand crimp on top and sloper on left and top out.   It's a fun short problem with the crux being the top out portion up the front of the boulder.

name: O.B.D.
description: Sit start. Begin with left in positive pocket, your in one of the few shallow two finger pockets. Fire your way up to slopey crimps, then into the slopers at top. Fantastic mantle at top.

name: Pinball
description: Work your way up the right arÃªte of the Yosemite slab.0

name: Praying Mantel
description: Start on crimps under the small roof, paste your feet and fire to the sloper lip. Establish your left hand on undercling, then try to figure out a way to mantle!

name: Pulling the Wool
description: Begin matched on jug, do a few moves up on crimps, then left into the arÃªte and up.

name: Toss Your Shoes Up
description: Fun little boulder problem! Sit start matched on rail, find feet and work your way up. Many variations exist. You can also work left onto the Arete which is fun as well. If there is another name for this please make the change. You can toss your shoes up and put them on, on top so you donât have to walk through all the moss and mud.Â

name: Wolverine
description: Start on the obvious jug and dyno to the chalked up sloper.

name: Yosemite Slab
description: Huge, grand, stunning. Walk your way up the perfect slab.

name: Young Thugz Post-Break
description: Start on two small thunderclings with horrible feet, throw for the jug. Traverse right and up through the jugs  NOTE:Â The start holds to this problem likely broke sometime after its 03/20/09 FA, making itÂ harder.The best guess based on the first ascensionistâs opinion and the (only?)Â 2 other ascents of the Pre-Break version put its difficulty at ~V9.The first ascensionist of the original Young Thugs repeated the Post-Break version on 10/30/20 and proposed a tentative grade of V11 (as well as the name âCum Thugzâ).Additionally, while the Pre-Break version was a drop off problem from the jug ledge out right, the newly re-opened Post-Break version tops out the entire boulder (via V0- jug hauling).Also, this is not a jump start, but starting from a 2 (or more) pad stack is totally legit. As long as you establish on the start (first crux) before thrutching to the jug pocket (second crux), youâre golden. Due to the way-more-subjective-than-normal nature of one move wonders, grade opinions for this problem would be much appreciated.

name: Zig Zag
description: The original start begins on two crimp side pulls, but the start holds and feet tend to be wet, so you may have to start in the next couple holds. Pull through the crimps into nice positive holds, then lean back on gastons. Then fight through slopers near the end.

name: Alto Chili Bowl
description: Climb the featured face. Follow the bolt line and pull through good holds to reach the top

name: The Cradler
description: Climb through the steep face on good holds

name: Dr. Feel Good
description: Start up the easy face to a hard sequence using poor feet.

name: Geometrics
description: Begin by climbing left of the arete. Use good holds on the arete to access a blocky rail on the left. Continue through tricky moves to the top.

name: Know Your Grammar
description: Climb the face using big holds and easy moves

name: Phillip's Route
description: Start on good holds traversing up and left. Use the obvious but not so positive slot for the left hand and rock up to a slopeyish crimp. Make the clip and utilize the rest, the hard part is over. Locate the secret jug for clipping the 3rd. Once you hit the lip it's positive holds to the chains. Quite possibly the best route at the Pass.

name: Rendleman's
description: Begin on Dr. Feel Good, but immediately move right after clipping the first bolt. Climb to cool iron blobs.

name: Sir Mix-a-Lot
description: Mixed, climb the protectable crack to a single bolt. Anchors are over the second ledge.

name: Sprecher Brew Co
description: Climb through good holds through a leftward leaning fin. Pull over the top of the feature and clip the anchor

name: Stop Pass
description: Begin pulling on good flakes and climb into the scoop. Work to get high feet and pull the small bulge using a good left hold and a pocket. Continue through good holds to the top.

name: Swamp Hog
description: Probably should stick clip the first. Start on not so positive holds below the first bolt (fairly engaging). You may think it's in the bag after clipping the 2nd and 3rd but another crux awaits before the chains. Keep it together. Great rests on this route with some cool holds and interesting moves.  Note: For an easier start you can also traverse in from the shared start of the routes that begin to the right. But I recommend doing it as it was first done. Treat yourself don't cheat yourself. :-)

name: Ticket To Ride
description: Climb just left of the corner, work your way up to the seam and continue to the top

name: Streakin Johnny
description: Begin in the left crack. Work your way up to a small roof, cut left with the crack, and continue up.

name: Sweet Knockers
description: Climb the right crack, protecting when necessary. When the main crack system ends, pull over a small roof and climb the last crack section and top out the route.

name: Draft Root Beer
description: Start on the arete, and begin pulling through good holds. Angle up and right moving through a good side pull and edges to reach the anchor

name: Fitz's
description: Beginning on Draft Root Beer, climb up through the first two bolts. From here climb up and right and clip from a good jug. Work the difficult traverse into a corner. Clip again and climb the corner up to a large block jug and eventually around the arete. Clip again again and pull to the anchor.    5.8 Variation: Shown in RED on the beta photo. Bypass the tough traverse section and  Layback the crack as a more direct start for the route. Traditionally protect when necessary to reach the bolted line.

name: Mr. Frosty
